  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">Third defense of the year. Higher stakes than U1 or U2.</p>
  <p>Unit 4's defense day. <a href="/units/unit-4/assessment-chennai-climate-brief/">Briefs</a> are submitted in the first 10 minutes; the next 60 is the Policy Panel itself — 4-min pitch + 3-min Q&amp;A per student, with peers playing Greater Chennai Corporation officials asking <strong>cost</strong>, <strong>feasibility</strong>, <strong>equity</strong>, and <strong>science-credibility</strong> questions. Higher-stakes format than U1's NASA Committee Defense (3+2) or U2's planning-audience share-out (3+2) — longer pitch, longer Q&amp;A, and the question categories are sharper.</p>
  <p>The block closes with a unit-close reflection on <em>climate engagement beyond this unit</em>, then a connect-forward to <a href="/units/unit-5/">Unit 5</a> — water is the climate system's central currency; U5 looks at it directly.</p>
</section>

