<section class="block-section concepts" style="margin-top:24px;">
  <span class="section-tag">Preview — Unit 5</span>
  <h2>Where we go next</h2>
  <p>Unit 5 asks: <strong>how do you decide who gets water?</strong> Water is the climate system's central currency — the variable everything else routes through. In Chennai, water is also the most contested resource, all the way down. Unit 5 anchors on the <a href="/foundations/eal/u5/">Cauvery water dispute</a> and similar stakeholder cases. You'll take a stakeholder perspective, write a Position Paper from that perspective, and defend it in a multi-stakeholder Roundtable. Same audience-awareness muscle you just built — applied to a case where the audience has competing claims, not shared interests.</p>
  <p>The frameworks you used this unit (OPVL on IPCC + government sources, AI Documentation, policy-brief voice, Policy Panel defense) carry forward. If something feels shaky from Unit 4, the <a href="/foundations/">Foundations</a> pages stay live all year — and the <a href="/units/unit-4/">Unit 4 landing</a> isn't going anywhere either.</p>
</section>
